The paper focuses on the usage and effectiveness of academic social networking sites, which involves aspects of information retrieval (IR), digital libraries (DL), and social computing (SOC). The study also involves qualitative content analysis, which is commonly used in the field of computational social science (SI). Additionally, the paper examines the practices of scholars in different disciplines, including library and information services (CY), history of art, and astrophysics.
